                            <comment id="12899679" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 18 Aug 2010 00:59:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tripped into that one too today, along with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2522&quot; title=&quot;Disabling a table during a split (tricky) can leave the daughter regions assigned and marked offline in .META.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2522&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2522&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Seriously reduced my ability to fix the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918705" author="nspiegelberg" created="Wed, 6 Oct 2010 22:09:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue should be resolved by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2819&quot; title=&quot;hbck should have the ability to repair basic problems&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2819&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2819&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  You can run &apos;bin/hbase hbck -fix&apos; instead of &apos;close_region&apos; to fix this.  Close this issue as a subset of the other?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13219541" author="stack" created="Wed, 29 Feb 2012 21:00:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tried it and it is still broke though it seems different.&lt;/p&gt;

